article.description: Tyaunna Marshall scored 21 points and had the go-ahead basket with 1:35 left to help Georgia Tech (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) beat North Carolina 54-53 in Friday's quarterfinals of the Atlantic Coast Conference tournament.
article.headline: Tyaunna Marshall scores 21 in Georgia Tech's quarterfinal win
article.linkText: Marshall lifts Ga. Tech by UNC in ACC quarters
article.story:
GREENSBORO, N.C. --  Tyaunna Marshall scored 21 points and had the go-ahead basket with 1:35 left to help Georgia Tech (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) beat North Carolina 54-53 in the quarterfinals of the Atlantic Coast Conference tournament Friday.


Mo Bennett and Metra Walthour each scored 11 for the fourth-seeded Yellow Jackets (23-7), who held on when Brittany Rountree's long 3-pointer for the win bounced off the front of the rim at the horn.

Georgia Tech reached the semifinals for the third straight season and will face ninth-seeded North Carolina State, which upset Duke (No. 6 ESPN/USA Today, No. 5 AP).

She'la White scored 13 points for the fifth-seeded Tar Heels (20-11), who lost twice to Georgia Tech this month by a combined three points. North Carolina rallied from seven down to go up four with about 4 minutes left and set up a back-and-forth finish.


UNC's Chay Shegog hit a jumper for a 53-52 with 2:06 left before Marshall answered on the ensuing possession.
